 Willowvale police on Wednesday arrested a 27-year-old man for the possession of unlicensed firearm - a shotgun. "The suspect was arrested at Bonde Locality, in Bojini Village, Willowvale," said police spokesperson, Captain Jackson Manatha. "Willowvale police were visible and conducting patrols when they noticed the suspect carrying the firearm." He said that the suspect was arrested as he had no license to possess the firearm. "The weapon had no ammunition." Captain Manatha added that the suspect will appear before the Willowvale Magistrate's Court on Thursday. 